title: [Vornavian Coast, North Beach]
description: The beach widens to the south, but narrows to the north from this section of shoreline.  A row of driftwood lines the beach, washed ashore by the ends of waves which exhaust themselves on the black sands.

The beach widens to the south, but narrows to the north from this section of shoreline.  A flock of seagulls stands near the tide, seemingly washing their feet in the ends of waves which exhaust themselves on the black sands.
